# Patterns here match the TARGET path (relative to $HOME), gitignore-style.

# ─── Repo documentation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These describe the source repo; they are not dotfiles. Without this block
# `chezmoi apply` writes them to ~/README.md etc. (`chezmoi status` shows them
# as `A`), littering $HOME. Leading slash anchors to $HOME so that a nested
# README.md elsewhere in the target tree is still applied normally.
/README.md
/X11_TO_WAYLAND_TRANSITION.md
/MACOS_PORTING_GUIDE.md
/CHEZMOI_UPDATE_WORKFLOW.md
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/LICENSE

# ─── Browser profiles ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Browser-generated profiles stay local. They contain bookmarks, account/sync
# identifiers, site-engagement records, and other machine-generated state.
# The sanitized Zen user.js allowlist is installed by the profile-discovery
# script without exposing or managing the rest of the profile.
.config/net.imput.helium/
.var/app/app.zen_browser.zen/
